Package: s4
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${cargo:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Recommends: python3 (>= 3.9)
Suggests:
 python3-construct,
 python3-defusedxml,
 python3-pycryptodome,
Description: speedily search and merge log messages by datetime
 s4 is a command-line tool to search and merge varying log messages from
 varying log files, sorted by datetime. Datetime filters may be passed to
 narrow the search to a datetime range.
 .
 s4 can read standardized log message formats like RFC 3164 and RFC 5424
 (syslog), Red Hat Audit logs, strace output, dmesg and X.org logs, and
 can read many non-standardized ad-hoc log message formats, including
 multi-line log messages. It also parses binary accounting records acct,
 lastlog, and utmp (acct, pacct, lastlog, utmp, utmpx, wtmp), systemd
 journal logs (.journal), Windows Event Logs (.evtx), Windows Event Trace
 Logs (.etl), OneDrive Log files (.odl, .aodl, .odlgz, .odlsent), and
 Apple System Logs (.asl). s4 can read logs that are compressed (.bz2,
 .gz, .lz4, .xz), or archived logs (.tar).
 .
 For Windows ETL and OneDrive ODL file support, s4 uses Python helper
 scripts that are embedded in the binary. Run 's4 --venv' to create the
 Python virtual environment. The suggested packages (python3-construct,
 python3-defusedxml, python3-pycryptodome) cover dependencies available
 in Debian. Additional dependencies not yet packaged for Debian
 (colorist, dissect.etl, dissect.cstruct, etl-parser, inputimeout) can
 be installed via pip into the virtual environment created by 's4 --venv'.
